Description: A made up roll of papyrus wrapped in textile bands. Stored in a box with EA 76536-56.
Curator's comments: Previously unregistered material stored in Papyrus Store. These modern 'made-up' rolls have been kept as examples of the phenomenon.
Exhibition history: Oct 2015, Grenoble, PCI scanning project 2022-2023 13 Oct-19 Feb, London, BM, Hieroglyphs: unlocking ancient Egypt
